text: Tallabogue is a stream in the U.S. state of Mississippi. It is a tributary to Tuscolameta Creek. Tallabogue is a name derived from the Choctaw language purported to mean "palmetto creek". Variant names are "Taalah Creek" and "Tallabogue Creek". ==References== Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Scott County, Mississippi
title: Tallabogue (Tuscolameta Creek tributary)
